Mirrors in dreams symbolize self‑reflection, identity, and emotional truth. They reveal how you see yourself—or how you fear others see you.

If you see a clear reflection, the dream suggests self‑awareness and honesty. You may be gaining clarity about who you are or what you want.

A distorted reflection symbolizes insecurity or confusion. You may be struggling with self‑image or feeling disconnected from your true self.

If you cannot see your reflection at all, the dream may reflect uncertainty about your identity or direction. You may feel lost or unsure about your role in a situation.

Breaking a mirror symbolizes transformation. You may be letting go of old beliefs or breaking free from limiting self‑perceptions.

Mirrors are powerful dream symbols because they force you to confront your inner truth. They reveal what you believe about yourself—and what you may need to change.
